replies.bodyText:
A deployment can take hours or even days, for example, if the device is offline and the packages cannot be downloaded, or if one of the services are performing critical tasks and cannot be interrupted.
The intention is the thread will be blocked until:

the future is finished;
the future is cancelled;
the thread is interrupted.

The caller can always cancel it or interrupt the thread if it decides not to wait any longer (e.g. a new deployment comes in).

